Apple (NASDAQ:AAPL) might be in line for a strong holiday season of iPhone sales in China based on recent information about how shipments in the country performed last month. 
 
In a research note, J.P. Morgan analyst Samik Chatterjee said that data from the China Academy of Information and Communications Technology shows that Apple (AAPL) shipped 10.8 million iPhone in the country during October.
